                             Golden Mouse Award


              Tauzin, Greenwood Want More Details From Andersen

   Washington (January 29) – Building on last week’s Oversight
   Subcommittee hearing on destruction of Enron-related documents by
   Andersen LLP, House Energy and Commerce Committee Chairman Billy Tauzin
   (R-LA) and Oversight and Investigations Subcommittee Chairman James
   Greenwood (R-PA) today called on the accounting firm to produce
   additional information relevant to the Committee’s far-reaching probe
   into Enron’s financial collapse. More...
     * Tauzin, Greenwood Want Law Firm Review Of Enron’s Related-Party
       Transactions
     * Letter Requesting Information Concerning Kenneth Lay's Enron Stock
       Transactions
     * Released Hearing Documents
     * Audio Archive of Hearing
       (The free Real Player required)
     * Tauzin Delivers Statement
       On Andersen’s Destruction
       of Enron Records
     * Tauzin Releases Letter From Enron Whistleblower
     * More on Enron Investigation



   Tauzin Hails House Passage of Sweeping Bioterrorism Bill

   "This sweeping package includes everything from beefed up food safety
   regulations to tightened controls on deadly biological agents.  In
   short, this bill, when signed into law by President Bush, will improve
   our ability to respond effectively and quickly to bioterrorist threats
   and other public health emergencies.” More...

